UNITED Party for National Development (UPND) president Hakainde Hichilema and economic experts have welcomed the government's mooted measures to resuscitate the national economy. On Monday, Cabinet resolved to restore macroeconomic stability on an upward trajectory for the benefits of Zambians, as it moves to cancel all project loans not disbursed. The experts yesterday called for quick implementation of the measures to salvage the economy and emphasised on adherence.